The violation is the ISP principle. The `NotificationSender` interface has methods for sending different types of notifications (email, SMS, push notification, Slack message), which are not all applicable to every service that implements it. This violates the Interface Segregation Principle because clients should not be forced to depend on interfaces they do not use.

